41 SECTION 3.
42 Said chapter is further amended by revising Code Section 43-5-7, relating to license
43 requirement for persons engaged as athletic trainers, as follows:
44 "43-5-7.
45 No person shall hold himself or herself out as an athletic trainer or perform the services of
46 an athletic trainer, as defined in this chapter, without first obtaining a license under this
47 chapter. Nothing; provided, however, that nothing in this chapter shall be construed to
48 prevent any person enrolled in an accredited athletic training educational program
49 recognized by the board from serving as a student-trainer, assistant-trainer, or any similar
50 position an athletic training student if such service is not primarily for compensation
51 following the accredited program's standards for clinical education and is carried out under
52 the direct supervision of a physician or a licensed athletic trainer. As used in this Code
53 section, the term 'direct supervision' means that the supervising athletic trainer or physician
54 is physically present in the facility where athletic training students assisting with athletic
55 training services are located and is immediately available to assist the person being
56 supervised."
57 SECTION 4.
58 Said chapter is further amended by revising Code Section 43-5-8, relating to qualifications
59 of applicants and reciprocity, as follows:
60 "43-5-8.
61 (a) An applicant for an athletic trainer's license must have met the athletic training
62 curriculum requirements of a college or university approved shall be a graduate of an
63 accredited educational program that prepares athletic trainers recognized by the board and
64 give proof of graduation or shall submit, in a manner prescribed by the board, equivalent
65 educational credentials as approved by the board.
